The N3 south is currently closed between the Marlboro and London Road offramps. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Two guards have been injured following a cash-in-transit heist on the N3 in Johannesburg on Saturday. READ: Five suspected CIT robbers shot dead in Boksburg The N3 south was closed between the Marlboro and London Road offramps. The vehicle suspected to have rammed a security van was on fire but has since been extinguished. Police are investigating the case. No arrests have yet been made and police have not released information on how much cash was stolen.